,
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation No 136/66/EEC of 22 September 1966 on the establishment of a common organization of the market in oils and fats (1), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 3179/93 (2), and in particular Article 5 (5) thereof,
Whereas Commission Regulation (EEC) No 3061/84 (3), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 2830/94 (4), lays down time limits for the payment of production aid for olive oil;
Whereas, in order to comply with the undertakings made in the agreement on agricultural prices in July 1994 regarding the time limits for the payment of aid, including advances, to producers and in order to help establish a payments system which can be  managed more efficiently, more precise time limits should be laid down for the payment of aid;
Wheras the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Oils and Fats,
